  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ambiguous requirement)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package contains an adversarial weakness: the governing Requirement is stated in language that admits multiple plausible interpretations—specifically, 'acceptable hemolytic performance' and 'minimal additional hemolytic burden' are used without citation to any normative threshold document, leaving compliance underspecified.",
